BCrypt implements OpenBSD-style Blowfish password hashing using the scheme described in "A Future-Adaptable Password Scheme" by Niels Provos and David Mazieres.

The Book class represents a book in the library system.

The User class represents a user in the system with unique attributes and roles.

Represents roles that a user can have within the system.

UserDAO is a data access object class for performing CRUD operations on the User table in the database.

The UserService class provides methods to manage user operations such as registration.
